 Former BBniaja housemate Yerins Abraham, says, he will be putting medicine on hold for now because he enjoys Fashion and Art for now. In his interview with the “Sunday Scoop”, he said: “I’ve ways wanted to do fashion because is comprises of relaxation and boundless, my Fashion brand will be launched next year, an Art exhibition will be held soon that’s what am focusing on for now. READ ALSO: “Cut Your Coats Wisely” – Yerins Advises Fans “I’m not fully putting a hold on Medicine, is just that I’ll be working as a researcher. I wrote my medical examination at 111countries which Nigeria and Ghana are going excluded.” “I’ve been offered a certificate which come along with Stamp of Apostille to practice in all participating countries of Hague convention of 1961,” Yerins said. Well, it looks like our star is going to do well in the Fashion business and his fans are looking forward for that.